00:23.699 --> 00:25.630
If the compass continues
pointing us south,

00:25.631 --> 00:27.298
we'll go right past
the Falls of Aldermont.

00:27.299 --> 00:28.434
Is that someplace important?

00:28.435 --> 00:30.203
It's considered
the most romantic spot

00:30.204 --> 00:31.768
in all the Midlands.

00:31.769 --> 00:35.597
Many a child was conceived
beneath those cascading waters.

00:35.598 --> 00:37.463
I was there once.
It's beautiful.

00:37.464 --> 00:39.125
Oh, really?
And who were you with?

00:39.126 --> 00:40.921
My sister.

00:40.922 --> 00:44.255
At sunset,
when the light hits the falls,

00:44.256 --> 00:46.558
the water glistens red.

00:46.559 --> 00:49.226
They say it's the reflection
of all the lovers' hearts

00:49.227 --> 00:51.291
who've kissed there.

00:51.292 --> 00:53.358
That or a reflection
of the blood spilled

00:53.359 --> 00:54.625
at the Battle of Aldermont.

00:54.626 --> 00:58.191
Two hundred men were
killed in that spot.

00:58.192 --> 00:59.890
The rest threw their bodies
into the rapids

00:59.891 --> 01:01.123
rather than surrender.

01:01.124 --> 01:02.623
Well, that does sound romantic.

01:02.624 --> 01:05.059
( chuckles )
If we move fast,

01:05.060 --> 01:06.593
we can get there
in time to see the sunset.

01:08.662 --> 01:10.595
( <i>ominous theme playing</i> )

01:18.765 --> 01:21.366
(Cara)
These men were tortured.

01:21.367 --> 01:23.500
Not very inspired work.

01:23.501 --> 01:25.401
(Richard)
Looks like they died
before they hung.

01:25.402 --> 01:27.702
Then why hang them?

01:27.703 --> 01:29.869
Whoever did this wanted
to put them on display

01:29.870 --> 01:32.238
to send a message.

01:32.239 --> 01:34.906
(Zedd)
"Whoever attempts
to subvert justice

01:34.907 --> 01:37.241
shall meet the same fate."

01:37.242 --> 01:38.609
Kahlan, take a look at this.

01:41.612 --> 01:43.145
It's the seal of Aydindril.

01:46.381 --> 01:47.914
"By order
of the High Lord Regent."

01:47.915 --> 01:49.581
Who's that?

01:49.582 --> 01:50.715
There's no such title.

01:50.716 --> 01:52.082
The only person
with the authority

01:52.083 --> 01:55.051
to confer this seal
is the Mother Confessor.

01:55.052 --> 01:57.619
Then who ordered
these men killed?

01:59.154 --> 02:01.088
( <i>dramatic theme playing</i> )

02:03.691 --> 02:05.791
(Man)
I can pay you
15 gold pieces now.

02:05.792 --> 02:08.658
I'll have the rest soon,
I promise.

02:08.660 --> 02:10.461
Please, Lord Regent,

02:10.461 --> 02:11.995
give me a little more time.

02:11.996 --> 02:14.263
You've had more than a month.

02:14.264 --> 02:15.964
It's been difficult
for me to find work

02:15.965 --> 02:16.964
since you cut off my hand.

02:16.965 --> 02:18.165
Your hand was removed

02:18.166 --> 02:19.966
as punishment
for stealing grain.

02:19.967 --> 02:21.200
Times were hard after the war.

02:21.201 --> 02:22.334
My family needed food.

02:22.335 --> 02:24.235
You were tried fairly
and found guilty.

02:24.236 --> 02:26.070
In accordance with the law,
you lost your hand.

02:26.071 --> 02:28.137
Wasn't that punishment enough?

02:28.138 --> 02:30.472
For theft?

02:30.473 --> 02:31.772
But to steal that grain,

02:31.773 --> 02:35.008
you also trespassed
on Olrich Larson's land.

02:35.009 --> 02:36.742
Should that crime
simply go unpunished?

02:36.743 --> 02:38.710
If the Council and the Mother
Confessor were here,

02:38.711 --> 02:39.710
they would never allow--

02:39.711 --> 02:42.178
But they aren't here, are they?

02:43.480 --> 02:44.813
Please.

02:44.814 --> 02:46.581
Have mercy...

02:46.582 --> 02:47.915
( scoffs )

02:47.916 --> 02:49.249
I'm showing you mercy, Shaun.

02:49.250 --> 02:52.018
Fifty gold pieces
and you can go home.

02:52.019 --> 02:53.519
I don't have it.

02:53.520 --> 02:57.255
Please don't take my other hand.

02:57.256 --> 02:59.323
Oh, I'm not going
to take your other hand.

03:02.192 --> 03:05.360
Tomorrow at dawn,
cut off his head.

03:05.361 --> 03:08.429
No! No!

03:08.430 --> 03:10.130
No, please don't kill me! No!

03:10.131 --> 03:12.198
No!

03:12.199 --> 03:14.799
My family will starve!
Don't do this!

03:14.800 --> 03:16.434
You see why I asked you to come.

03:16.435 --> 03:19.669
I only wish I could
have gotten here sooner.

03:19.670 --> 03:22.471
Fyren's army
is occupying the city.

03:22.472 --> 03:24.039
The people are afraid
to oppose him.

03:24.040 --> 03:27.408
Even a Wizard of the Second
Order might find himself

03:27.409 --> 03:28.642
swinging from a noose

03:28.643 --> 03:30.944
if he tried to use
magic to stop him.

03:30.945 --> 03:32.011
I need your help.

03:32.012 --> 03:34.880
What about Oloron's Amulet?

03:34.881 --> 03:36.481
Fyren has it locked
in the treasury

03:36.482 --> 03:39.016
with a dozen men guarding it.

03:39.017 --> 03:40.984
I'll get it.
(Fyren) The next prisoner.

03:40.985 --> 03:44.620
There are not many Wizards
left in this world, Silas.

03:44.621 --> 03:46.955
Going in there would--
Would be tantamount

03:46.956 --> 03:48.522
to signing your own
death warrant.

03:48.523 --> 03:51.424
And how many more
death warrants will be signed

03:51.425 --> 03:54.926
if we don't bring the Mother
Confessor back to Aydindril?

03:57.463 --> 04:00.230
( <i>dramatic theme playing</i> )

04:00.231 --> 04:02.165
( chatter )

04:03.633 --> 04:05.834
Halt, Wizard.

04:05.835 --> 04:06.968
Halt or I'll shoot.

04:06.969 --> 04:09.803
( chanting in ancient tongue )

04:09.804 --> 04:11.103
( grunting )

04:13.000 --> 04:19.074
Advertise your product or brand here
